      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IM DOWNBYTHEBEACH NZ (7) is better than what he showed last start having kicked off in Australia with a win at Melton before a second at Bendigo, both in higher-graded races than this. Gets a soft run on the inside of the second line and can win if he gets the gaps. SEASIDE BOULEVARD (5) is progressive and did a good job for a winning return at Wagga last week. That took her record at this distance range to two from three. Lightly raced with upside and is a big chance to keep the ball rolling. EYE WISH (6) is race fit now and could be close to a win after placing in all three starts this time in, the latest a third from this barrier at Wagga. SHEZAGLAMOURGIRL (4) placed fresh then finished fourth last start at Bendigo. Has switched yards and had seven weeks off since but has trialled and goes well at this distance with a win and two placings from three attempts.",
